h3. Problem Definition

JIRA has experimental REST API operations to change and fetch issue properties:
{code}/rest/api/2/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/properties/{propertyKey}{code}

This is available in [JIRA REST API documentation|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/#api/2/issue/\{issueIdOrKey\}/properties].

The 'set property' operation (a PUT operation) seems to require a request payload to actually set the property. Something like the response from the 'get property' operation:
{code}
{
    "key": "issue.support",
    "value": {
        "hipchat.room.id": "support-123",
        "support.time": "1m"
    }
}
{code}

However, this is not described in the documentation and may be confusing.

h3. Suggested Solution

Like in the [create issue|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/#api/2/issue-createIssue] documentation, add a 'request example' to 'set property'. The data above may be used.

